          "text" : "Overview",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "The Swift extension provides pre-release builds that you can use to test out unreleased features or get bug fixes before the project publishes an official release. Pre-release build numbers are one minor version ahead of the most recent release.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "The “Switch to Pre-Release Version” button in the VS Code extensions view is used to install the latest pre-release builds:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "identifier" : "install-pre-release.png",
              "type" : "image"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "When you select to use a pre-release version, the button changes to “Switch to Release Version”, which lets you go back to the official release.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind" : "content"
    }
